    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ad" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ad</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>adæ</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>вкус</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>taste</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>adǵyn</orth></form>
                    <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>вкусный</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>tasty</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>сладкий</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>sweet</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                </re>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>adginag</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сладость</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>sweet</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>xærzad xærīnag</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">вкусная пища</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">tasty food</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>cæxx jæ ad k˳y fesafa, wæd æj cæmæj ysræstmæ ḱyndæ wa?</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>если соль потеряет силу (вкус), чем исправить ее?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Salt is good: but if the salt have lost his savour, wherewith shall
                                it be seasoned?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Лука"/><biblScope>%i14%i
                            34</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Pupæ Asiaty k˳y næ wyny, … wæd yn card ad næ kæny</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>когда Пупа не видит Асиат, то жизнь ему не в сладость</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>when Pupa does not see Asiat, life is not sweet for him</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>20</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>aci suǧzærīnæ ærdo ke særiǧunæj æj, e mæ osæn ku næ wa, wæd mænæn mæ
                            card adæ næbal iskænʒænæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>если та, из чьих волос эта золотая волосинка, не станет моей женой,
                                то жизнь будет мне не в сладость</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>if the one from whose hair this single golden hair is does not become
                                my wife, then life will not be sweet to me</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."
                            /><biblScope>10%l8%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>adǵyn xærīnagæj je stong næ bæsasta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>вкусной пищей он (никогда) не утолил свой голод</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he has (never) satisfied his hunger with tasty food</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>67</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>adǵyn caj cymʒynæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ты будешь пить сладкий чай</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>you are going to drink sweet tea</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"
                            /><biblScope>121</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>mæ adgin iwazægi min ewʒæstug fækkodta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>моего милого гостя сделал одноглазым</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he made my dear guest one-eyed</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."
                            /><biblScope>32%l14%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>mady qæbysaw dyn adǵyn wæd acy zæxx</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>да будет эта земля тебе приятна, как материнское лоно</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>may this land be pleasant to you like a mother's womb</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>78</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>næ rajg˳yræn, næ bæstæ, cardæn adǵyn dy k˳y dæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>наша родная, наша страна, ведь ты (одна) сладка для жизни</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>our dear, our country, after all you are (the only one) sweet for
                                life</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 104</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Происхождение слова не ясно: к корню *%ied%i- ‘есть’ (<mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>ad-</w>
                        <gloss><q>есть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>ādya-</w>
                        <gloss><q>съедобный</q></gloss></mentioned>)? к <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>odor</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>hot</w>
                        <gloss><q>запах</q></gloss></mentioned>? <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>éz</w>
                        <gloss><q>вкус</q></gloss></mentioned> считается усвоенным из осетинского
                    (аланского) (<bibl><author>Munkàcsi</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_KSz."
                            /><biblScope>V 315</biblScope></bibl>); для чередования ос. %id%i —
                        <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>z</w></mentioned> ср. ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_būd"/> ‘ладан’ —
                        <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>büd</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>fid-</w>
                        <gloss><q>платить</q></gloss></mentioned> — <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>fizet</w></mentioned>, ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qæd_1"/> ‘лес’ —
                        <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>gaz</w></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"
                            /><biblScope>III 167</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>38</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                            /><biblScope>18</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">The etymology is not clear; could it trace back to the root
                    *%ied%i- ‘eat’ (<mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>ad-</w>
                        <gloss><q>eat</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>ādya-</w>
                        <gloss><q>edible</q></gloss></mentioned>)? to <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>odor</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>hot</w>
                        <gloss><q>smell</q></gloss></mentioned>? <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>éz</w>
                        <gloss><q>taste</q></gloss></mentioned> is considered to be borrowed from
                    Ossetic (Alan) (<bibl><author>Munkàcsi</author><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_KSz."/><biblScope>V 315</biblScope></bibl>); for the
                    alternation Ossetic %id%i — Hungarian %iz%i cf. Ossetic <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_būd"/> ‘frankincense’ — <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>büd</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>fid-</w>
                        <gloss><q>pay</q></gloss></mentioned> — <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>fizet</w></mentioned>, Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qæd_1"/>
                    ‘forest’ — <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>gaz</w></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"
                            /><biblScope>III 167</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>38</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                            /><biblScope>18</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
